
[1]chord

   CHORD, n.

   1. The string of a musical instrument.

   2. In music, the union of two or more sounds uttered at the same time,
   forming an entire harmony; as a third, fifth and eighth, which are
   perfect chords, or consonancies. The fourth and sixth are imperfect
   chords.

   3. In geometry, a right line drawn or supposed to extend from one end
   of an arch of a circle to the other. Hence the chord of an arch is a
   right line joining the extremities of that arch.

                           CHORD, v.t. To string.
